The paper deals with cooperative multi-agent reinforcement learning, which is a subfield of machine learning and artificial intelligence. The use of neural networks and value decomposition networks in particular suggests that the paper falls under the category of cs.LG (Machine Learning). The paper also deals with the problem of partial observability, which is a common issue in multi-agent systems, suggesting that it could also fall under cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). The focus on cooperative multi-agent learning suggests that it could also fall under cs.MA (Multi-Agent Systems). The use of weight sharing and role information suggests that it could also fall under cs.RO (Robotics). Finally, the use of information channels suggests that it could also fall under cs.SY (Systems and Control).
